!!!
%html
  %head
    %title Stories
    = haml :"templates/header_imports"
  %body
    %div{:class => ""}
      = haml :"templates/nav"

    %div{:class => "container"}
      %div{:class => "panel panel-default"}
        %div{:class => "panel-heading"}
          %h3{:class =>"panel-title"}
            Story wizard - Part II - Quiz

        %div{:class => "panel-body"}
          A quiz in Tag Story is of the yes-or-no type, and contain as many questions that you like. There can even be a little correction, or explenation for users picking the wrong answer.
          
      %div{:class => "panel panel-default"}
        %div{:class => "panel-heading"}
          %h3{:class =>"panel-title"}
            Quiz action
        %div{:class => "panel-body"}
          
          %form{:action => "/mystories/wizard/tag/camera", :method => "post", :role => "form", :class => "form-horizontal"}
            %fieldset
              - params.each_with_index do | elem, i |
                %div{:class => "panel panel-default"}
                  .panel-heading
                    %h3{:class => "panel-title"}
                      Question ##{i + 1}
                  .panel-body
                    %div{:class => "row form-group"}
                      %div{:class => "col-md-2"}
                        %label{:for => "question"} Question:
                      %input{:type => "text", :name => "quiz[][question]", :value => "#{elem['question']}"}    

                    %div{:class => "row form-group"}
                      %div{:class => "col-md-2"}
                        %label{:for => "answer"} Correct answer:
                      %input{:type => "text", :name => "quiz[][answer]", :value => "#{elem['answer']}"}

                    %div{:class => "row form-group"}
                      %div{:class => "col-md-2"}
                        %label{:for => "correction"} Correction:
                      %input{:type => "text", :name => "quiz[][correction]", :value => "#{elem['correction']}"}

              %div{:class => "row form-group buttons", :class => "col-md-5"}
                %input{:type => "submit", :name => "save", :value => "Save", :class => "btn btn-default"}
                %input{:type => "submit", :name => "add_quiz", :value => "Add question", :class => "btn btn-default"}
                
            %p
              When the user have taken and shared an image, you need to inform them where to go next. So let us make a direction to the next app.
              A direction is actually the same as a single question, but you can only have one direction when using the camera.
              %br
              At least for now. It may later be possible to send user to different location based on how they scored on the quiz.
                
            %br
            %a{:href => "/mystories/wizard/tag/quiz/direction", :class => "btn btn-default"}
              Direction
